.TH "wb_split_bdi_pages" 9 "wb_split_bdi_pages" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
wb_split_bdi_pages \- split nr_pages to write according to bandwidth
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "long" wb_split_bdi_pages
.BI "(struct bdi_writeback *wb "  ","
.BI "long nr_pages "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "wb" 12
target bdi_writeback to split \fInr_pages\fP to
.IP "nr_pages" 12
number of pages to write for the whole bdi
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Split \fIwb\fP's portion of \fInr_pages\fP according to \fIwb\fP's write bandwidth in
relation to the total write bandwidth of all wb's w/ dirty inodes on
\fIwb->bdi\fP.
